<body>
    <h1>Circles & Triangles</h1>
    <p>Circles have 360 degrees. When we place a triangle inside a circle, interesting relationships emerge between the arc lengths and the angles at each vertex. Explore these relationships by dragging the vertices or using the controls below.</p>

    <div id="main-container">
        <div id="canvas-container"></div>

        <div id="info-panel">
            <span class="info-header">Arc</span>
            <span class="info-header"></span>
            <span class="info-header">Vertex</span>
            <span class="info-header"></span>

            <span id="arc-label-1">Arc AB</span>
            <span id="arc-value-1">108°</span>
            <span id="vertex-label-1">Vertex C</span>
            <span id="vertex-value-1">54.0°</span>

            <span id="arc-label-2"></span>
            <span id="arc-value-2"></span>
            <span id="vertex-label-2"></span>
            <span id="vertex-value-2"></span>

